=== 7.4 The Code: Multi-Head Attention in Python

Each attention head is a triple of weight matrices stem:[(W_q, W_k, W_v)], each of shape stem:[[d \times d_k\]].
`MultiHeadAttention` groups the heads with the output projection stem:[W_o]; `make_multi_head_attention` allocates them.

[source,python]
----
include::../../../src/python/common.py[tag=mha_params]
----

`multi_head_attention` runs each head's SDPA independently, concatenates the per-head outputs column-wise, and applies the output projection.

[source,python]
----
include::../../../src/python/common.py[tag=mha_forward]
----

